        <h1>About Dr. Linda Bluestein</h1>
        <p>For many people living with hypermobility and connective tissue disorders, the journey to answers can be long and frustrating. Dr. Linda Bluestein understands this both as a physician and through her own lived experience.</p>
        <p>Dr. Bluestein practiced for many years as a board-certified anesthesiologist before shifting her professional focus to hypermobility disorders and the complex conditions that often accompany them. Today, she dedicates her work to helping individuals better understand and manage conditions such as hypermobile Ehlers-Danlos syndrome (hEDS), Hypermobility Spectrum Disorders (HSD), postural orthostatic tachycardia syndrome (POTS), mast cell activation, and chronic pain.</p>
        <p>Her path to this work was shaped in part by her own story. As a lifelong dancer, Dr. Bluestein experienced many of the injuries and physical challenges common in people with joint hypermobility. Later, she was diagnosed with hypermobile Ehlers-Danlos syndrome herself, providing firsthand insight into the complexities of these conditions&mdash;including the physical symptoms, the uncertainty that often accompanies them, and the search for effective strategies to improve quality of life.</p>
        <p>Combining her medical training with her personal experience, Dr. Bluestein has become a leading expert and advocate within the hypermobility community. She has lectured internationally, contributed to research and educational initiatives, and regularly shares information through the <a href="/podcast/">Bendy Bodies Podcast</a>, where she interviews leading experts in medicine, rehabilitation, and performing arts health. She is also the author of <a href="https://hypermobilitymd.substack.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">The Bendy Bulletin</a>, a newsletter dedicated to education and resources for people living with EDS, hypermobility, and related conditions.</p>
        <p>Through her <a href="/services/#coaching">EduCoaching</a> program, Dr. Bluestein works with individuals who want a deeper understanding of their condition and practical strategies for moving forward. EduCoaching focuses on education, guidance, and collaborative problem-solving, helping people navigate complex health challenges, communicate more effectively with their healthcare teams, and identify approaches that may improve function and quality of life.</p>
        <p>Dr. Bluestein also works as an integrative consultant alongside a patient's existing healthcare team. Her approach emphasizes understanding the many factors that can influence symptoms&mdash;from biomechanics and nervous system regulation to nutrition, sleep, and other aspects of health.</p>
        <p>Above all, she believes that when people better understand their bodies, they are better equipped to advocate for their health and make meaningful progress toward improved function and well-being.</p>
        <a href="/services/" class="btn btn-primary mt-2">Find the Right Support for You</a>
